results.name: Decimal expansion of Pi^Pi.
comment: A weak form of Schanuel's Conjecture implies that Pi^Pi is transcendental--see Marques and Sondow (2012).
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..20000
D. Marques and J. Sondow, The Schanuel Subset Conjecture implies Gelfond's Power Tower Conjecture, arXiv 2012.
program: (PARI) { default(realprecision, 20080); x=Pi^Pi/10; for (n=2, 20000, d=floor(x); x=(x-d)*10; write("b073233.txt", n, " ", d)); } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Apr 30 2009]
xref: Cf. A049006 (i^i), A116186 (real part of i^i^i).
results.author: _Rick L. Shepherd_, Jul 21 2002
